result.execSummary:
The defendant Gregory G. Paige was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:19 AM cases 22CF522, 21CF1004, 20CT282, 21CF1301, 21CM648 called. Defendant Gregory G. Paige in court, in custody.  Attorney Katherine Cook in court for Gregory G. Paige.  Prosecuting attorney Peter J. Rindal in court for the State of Wisconsin. State in compliance with victim notification requirements. 
Defense recites the joint agreement. Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
Defendant pleads No Contest to the following counts: 
In 21CF1301: Count 1 as charged in the Information. 
In 22CF522: Count 1 as charged in the Information. 

Defendant pleads Guilty to the following counts: 
21CF1301: Count 2 as charged in the Information. 
22CF522: Count 2 as charged in the Information. 
21CM648: Count 2 as charged in the Criminal Complaint. 
20CT282: Count 1 as charged in the Criminal Complaint. 
21CF1004: Counts 1 and 2 as charged in the Information. 

Court accepts pleas, finds the defendant Guilty.  Anything else is dismissed and read in. 
As to Count 1 in 20CT282 and Count 2 in 21CM648: Court orders defendant to pay court costs including applicable surcharges including 2 bench warrant fees in 20CT282. 

As to all other counts in which the defendant is found Guilty: 
Court withholds sentencing and places defendant on Probation for 2 on Count 1 in 22CF522 and Count 2 in 21CM648 and 30 months on remaining counts with conditions: 
Complete AODA and follow through with recommendations. 
Maintain absolute sobriety. Any conditions, programming or treatment per the agent and follow through with recommendations. 
No Contact with: UWEC campus, 507 Dodge Street in Eau Claire or Owen Park. 
No contact with any known drug dealers/users except in a therapeutic setting. 
No contact with T.J., J.V., A.J., M.M., D.K., M.C., J.L. 
Defendant not to go into bars, liquor stores or taverns. 
Defendant to pay court costs including applicable surcharges. 
As to Count 1 in 21CF1004 only: 90 days in Jail all Stayed pending further order of the Court. 

In 21CF1301: 4 days sentence credit, 21CF1004: 6 days sentence credit and 22CF522: 3 days sentence credit.
